article.headline: Musketeers threaten, but can't topple Terps
article.linkText: Langhorne's 18 and 11 lift Terps past Xavier
article.story:
CINCINNATI, Ohio (AP) -- Crystal Langhorne had 18 points and 11
rebounds, leading Maryland (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today; No. 22 AP) to a 74-72 win over Xavier on
Saturday.

Kalika France scored 13 of her 21 points in the second half for
Maryland (5-1).

Tara Boothe, helped by 9-for-10 shooting from the line, finished
with 23 points for Xavier (1-3).

Maryland led by as many as 12 points in the second half, before
the Musketeers closed within one point twice in the final eight
minutes.

Xavier had a chance to tie the score in the final seconds.
Maryland blocked a shot by Kristy Wallner, and Boothe caught the
loose ball but her 8-foot jumper missed as the buzzer sounded.

The Terrapins outscored Xavier 46-30 in the paint. Maryland also
had 15 offensive rebounds, and scored 19 second-chance points.

Maryland led 39-37 at the half.
